      "hypothesis": "The bot-excl-climbing family's losses concentrate in slow-to-graduate tape: binning v44-climb-1s live hours by hourly median_ttg showed slow (>=750s) hours at -8.3 mSOL/trade vs fast (<550s) at +2.2 mSOL/trade. median_ttg = rolling median of token_age_seconds, so the per-token, leak-free analogue is an upper age bound. v47 mirrors the v25 base (best family performer: +7.48 SOL / n=477 / drop3 +5.17) and adds token_age_seconds<750. Predict the age cap lifts per-trade edge vs the ungated v25 control without cutting n so hard it can't clear the bar.",
